opendial.bn.values

Interface Value

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<Value>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ArrayVal, BooleanVal, DoubleVal, Effect, NoneVal, ParseValue, SetVal, SpeechData, StringVal

    public interface Value
extends java.lang.Comparable<Value>
    Generic class for a variable value. The value can be:
    1. compared to other values
    2. copied in a new value
    3. check if it contains a sub-value
    4. concatenated with another value.
    .

    IMPORTANT: all implementations of Value must implement the three core methods equals(Object o), toString() and hashCode().

    Author:
    Pierre Lison (plison@ifi.uio.no)
